1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,840
And Music of the Week…

2
00:00:02,920 --> 00:00:05,840
MARS!

3
00:00:05,920 --> 00:00:06,920
Po!

4
00:00:11,160 --> 00:00:12,240
Let me… go home now.

5
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:14,080
You came home?

6
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:15,840
Wait. Are you saying you didn’t…

7
00:00:16,640 --> 00:00:17,816
I ruined last night’s date, didn’t I?

8
00:00:17,840 --> 00:00:20,160
Next time, I’ll watch a
movie at your place again.

9
00:00:22,920 --> 00:00:26,120
Can we say I'm your boyfriend now?

10
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:27,440
That's up to you.

11
00:00:28,040 --> 00:00:29,656
I don't know if you're
going to call me that,

12
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:30,760
but I will.

13
00:00:31,760 --> 00:00:32,800
My boyfriend.

14
00:01:12,960 --> 00:01:14,280
Why are you watching me sleeping?

15
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,400
Well…

16
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:18,760
you look cute.

17
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:45,479
Was… last night okay?

18
00:01:52,960 --> 00:01:53,960
Mm.

19
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:07,040
Do I really have to go
back to the group’s house

20
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:09,240
and check the music chart?

21
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:17,000
Are you staying here for good?

22
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,640
I want to, honestly.

23
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:28,520
It’s time for me to leave.

24
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:36,840
I’ll get going.

25
00:03:56,079 --> 00:03:56,920
One, two, three.

26
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,000
Yay!

27
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:00,800
Did we win that chart already?

28
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,240
Not yet.

29
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,080
- What are you guys celebrating for then?
- Come on.

30
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:07,200
We’re celebrating because
you’ve finally grown up.

31
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:08,840
Congrats, bro.

32
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:12,576
That's how it should be.
The student I’ve nurtured.

33
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:13,840
You? Come on.

34
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,200
Give me the credit, okay?

35
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,510
Eh?

36
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,176
You're number one when it
comes to taking credit, dude.

37
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,880
How is the chart going, by the way?

38
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:21,829
This one is pretty hard to climb.

39
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:23,600
If we rank number one,

40
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:26,240
we stand a high chance
to win the remaining three.

41
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,240
I already opened the page.

42
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:30,520
All you have to do is to
press the refresh button, man.

43
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:35,600
1. WOULD YOU MIND? - ICE

44
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:37,240
I’ll refresh now, okay?

45
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:38,480
Yeah.

46
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:40,520
I’ll do it now.

47
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,800
Uh-huh!

48
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:44,600
- I’ll do it for real now. - Yeah!

49
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,720
Damn it!

50
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,400
- Our song is number one! - For real?!

51
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:53,320
Woo-hoo!

52
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,680
Number one!

53
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:59,600
Great job.

54
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,920
- We did it, guys. - Great job.

55
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:03,000
We did it.

56
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,080
Great job, guys.

57
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:06,800
I need to tell my mommies now.

58
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:10,760
Let me check it one more time.

59
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:13,120
Eh? Where are you going?

60
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:19,920
ONLY THREE MORE CHARTS TO
GO AND WE’RE GOING TO PAK

61
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:23,040
I WISH YOU WERE HERE WITH ME NOW

62
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:23,960
Whoa.

63
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:25,360
Look at those crazy in love.

64
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:28,480
Those in love are annoying, aren’t they?

65
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,360
You’re right, Dylan.

66
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:34,080
Did I mishear that?

67
00:05:35,159 --> 00:05:36,720
You two actually agreed?

68
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:39,640
Oops, I don’t think so.

69
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:42,040
I bet it’s destiny.

70
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,960
You want a smack?

71
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,280
I’m kidding.

72
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:03,480
What’s up?

73
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,680
Did you see the leaked news about MARS?

74
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:08,720
Huh?

75
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:09,920
Check it now

76
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:13,680
because I think you can
explain the whole thing to me.

77
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:19,880
LEAKED IT! FAMOUS IDOL SPOTTED
BRINGING HIS SPECIAL SOMEONE TO HIS CONDO!

78
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:24,320
Do you have anything to say?

79
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:33,360
I saw the photos on my timeline already.

80
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,480
How long have you been hiding this?

81
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:37,600
Well,

82
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,200
I can explain it.

83
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:42,600
What’s the point of explaining it
now?! It’s too late, don’t you know?!

84
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,040
Hey.

85
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,680
I’m sorry.

86
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:48,880
- I just… - Why, Po?!

87
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:51,159
Why does it have to be my bias?

88
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,880
Why does it have to be Pepper?

89
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,736
LEAKED IT FAMOUS IDOL SPOTTED BRINGING
HIS SPECIAL SOMEONE TO HIS CONDO!

90
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:21,256
LET ME DIG UP MORE INFO #PEPPERMARS
REAL OR JUST FOR HYPE? #PEPPERMARS

91
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:23,080
CYBER DETECTIVES ON
THE CASE NOW! #PEPPERMARS

92
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:24,896
"WHO SAYS" IS BLOWING UP. MEMBER
SCANDAL LEAKS. IT'S OVER #PEPPERMARS

93
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:27,440
If the person you like likes someone else,

94
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:28,520
how do you feel?

95
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:31,096
SAYS HE LOVES US BUT SLEEPS
WITH ANOTHER WOMAN #PEPPERMARS

96
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,256
ARE THEY JUST USING FANS
FOR MONEY? #PEPPERMARS

97
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,800
If you don’t get it, then shut up.

98
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:35,536
SO LET DOWN. I DON'T WANT TO
SUPPORT HIM ANYMORE #PEPPERMARS

99
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,440
WHAT'S WRONG WITH THAT? HE
JUST HAS A GIRLFRIEND, RIGHT?

100
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:39,760
Being in an idol group means there are a
lot of rules and expectations to follow.

101
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:42,216
Telling the fans you love them
doesn't hit the same anymore

102
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,696
because your heart's
already with someone else.

103
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:44,936
I’LL STOP SUPPORTING THEM I
DON’T LIKE A LIAR #PEPPERMARS

104
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:45,760
See?

105
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:48,360
This is because a golden
rule for idols is that

106
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:50,440
they can’t be in a relationship.

107
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:51,976
PEPPER KNEW IT FULL WELL, BUT WHY DID
HE END UP DOING IT ANYWAY? #PEPPERMARS

108
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,936
I HAVE NO MORE PASSION TO SUPPORT HIM #PEPPERMARS
WHEN IS THE COMPANY RELEASING A STATEMENT? #PEPPERMARS

109
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:54,976
WE NEED YOUR ANSWER @ONERENTERTAINMENT

110
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:58,800
@ONERENTERTAINMENT WILL PROBABLY JUST PLAY DUMB
AGAIN @ONERENTERTAINMENT DON’T KEEP QUIET, OKAY?

111
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,880
Hello, yes?

112
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:03,920
Oh, if we’re having a press conference,

113
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,480
we’ll inform you later.

114
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:06,600
Yes. As for now,

115
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:09,000
- we couldn’t reach him yet.
- Yes. Goodbye.

116
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:10,280
Yes. Okay.

117
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,440
- Hello? Yes? - Hello?

118
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:16,920
Oh, I see.

119
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,040
Please give me a second.

120
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:21,040
Please hold the line for a
moment. I’ll transfer you.

121
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:27,880
HOW IS PEPPER NOW?

122
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:34,520
What did Gam say?

123
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,640
She told me to clear things
up with you guys first.

124
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,200
I’m sorry.

125
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:46,640
I… made everything worse.

126
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,560
Relax, bro.

127
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:51,120
Nothing is ruined, okay?

128
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:56,440
Let’s focus on both of you first.

129
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,520
How are you feeling now?

130
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:06,440
I think you should go be with her now.

131
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,920
How could I go?

132
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:14,520
- We’re now focusing on the
charts and... - We’ll take care of it.

133
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:18,360
Go to see her.

134
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,200
Be careful.

135
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:25,280
Don’t let anyone see you with Gam,

136
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:27,200
or else she will get dragged into this.

137
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:30,680
Avoid going to the condo.

138
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,520
Tell Gam

139
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:34,560
not to worry about it.

140
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,360
I don’t think anyone has the photo

141
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:39,240
that can identify it’s her.

142
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,600
But…

143
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,480
Go, bro.

144
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,280
I’m thanking you all on her behalf.

145
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:22,840
- Have you seen the news? - Yep.

146
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:25,280
This one, right?

147
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,920
Who do you think Pepper’s girlfriend is?

148
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,296
I have no idea. Her face isn’t seen.

149
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,320
Exactly.

150
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:47,456
I'm sorry you had to go through
something like this because of me.

151
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,480
Sit down.

152
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:52,920
Why are you saying sorry?

153
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:55,400
We’ve prepared for this since
our first day, haven’t we?

154
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:57,360
It’s true,

155
00:10:57,920 --> 00:11:00,240
but I’m still worried about
what’s going to happen to you.

156
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:01,680
I’m fine.

157
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,440
Fine?

158
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:04,800
Your situation is even worse.

159
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,560
With all this negative buzz,

160
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:08,136
it’s now even harder
for you to win the charts.

161
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:10,600
Your group reunion won’t be successful.

162
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:13,520
What should we do?

163
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:16,200
Has anyone taken any action?

164
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:19,440
Did they hold a press conference or
release the statement for the fans?

165
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:25,576
What should we do? Why is it that I can't
think of anything for stuff like this,

166
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,840
but I can come up with ideas
for other things so easily?

167
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:34,040
Why are you smiling?

168
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:35,560
Don’t you see that I’m stressed out?

169
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,880
I’m just impressed.

170
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:40,600
Instead of worrying about yourself,

171
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:43,840
you’re now trying to figure out
how to solve a problem for my group.

172
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:46,280
Why are you this adorable, huh?

173
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:51,920
I’m not adorable. I’m pretty.

174
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:56,040
Roger that. Got it.

175
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:57,160
Well…

176
00:11:57,720 --> 00:12:00,440
If anyone finds out it’s
me, I’m totally fine.

177
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:02,816
I’ve prepared for that since
the first day I started dating you.

178
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:06,040
So, now you should stop worrying about me

179
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:08,320
and prioritize your group and yourself.

180
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:09,400
Okay?

181
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,800
But I certainly won’t let this affect you.

182
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,800
I don’t want anything to happen to you.

183
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:31,280
Per, honestly,

184
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:34,760
I’m wondering why the
photos got leaked now.

185
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,936
Those photos were taken a
long time ago, weren't they?

186
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:39,200
Even before you returned
to the group’s house, right?

187
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:56,560
Yeah. Dylan said the same thing.

188
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:57,816
Someone intentionally leaked the photos.

189
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:59,416
That’s why I’m here at Oner to talk it out.

190
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:00,680
Let me know what she says.

191
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:01,760
Yeah. Talk to you later.

192
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:09,680
Ah. Here you are.

193
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,800
Miss Pemika asked for you.

194
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:18,160
And… Why is Po…

195
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:20,880
You will understand everything soon.

196
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:23,680
As for you, come with me. Now.

197
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,120
Are you asking for me too?

198
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:09,040
It’s about Pepper’s scandal.

199
00:14:10,520 --> 00:14:12,360
I thought we were on the same page.

200
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:15,040
I thought you’d allow MARS
to really prove ourselves,

201
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:17,440
but you’re doing this to get in our way.

202
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:22,720
You thought I leaked Pepper’s photos?

203
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:25,840
And you didn’t?

204
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:28,640
Yes, I did,

205
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:32,360
but it wasn’t for stopping
your song from winning the chart.

206
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:35,280
For what then?

207
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:44,720
To conceal this scandal.

208
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:55,040
Leak It sent me these photos,

209
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:56,800
saying they’d release this scandal.

210
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:58,840
I was left with not many choices.

211
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,880
I had to exchange the other
member’s news to save you,

212
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:05,280
or I had to pay Leak It to save you

213
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:08,520
because I won’t let this
ruin your fame, no matter what.

214
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:13,080
So, you chose to ruin Pepper’s instead?

215
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:19,360
Your value is higher than his, Thame.

216
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:25,280
You’re in my business
plan, but Pepper isn't.

217
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:28,240
To say it correctly,

218
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:31,280
both of you broke the rule.

219
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:33,000
Among these four,

220
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:35,320
saving you is already enough.

221
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,640
What did you do to Po?

222
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:44,840
So, the traitor I’ve been searching
for isn’t Jun, but Po, right?

223
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:47,480
What did you do to him?

224
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:52,080
And what do you think I should do

225
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:54,680
to the person who got in and
caused damage to the company?

226
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:59,000
Leave all of MARS’s footage with Tae.

227
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:01,120
You have no right to take any of it.

228
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:13,520
I’m sorry, but what’s going on?

229
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:27,840
But this whole thing isn’t his fault.

230
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:30,120
If you’re to punish someone for this,

231
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:32,440
it should be me.

232
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,000
Thame,

233
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:40,000
this industry doesn't revolve around
what’s right or wrong or fairness.

234
00:16:40,920 --> 00:16:43,440
It’s about who can sell more

235
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:45,360
and who the market demands.

236
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:50,480
And that person will always
appear spotless in everyone's eyes.

237
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:54,280
Right now, no matter
what mistakes you make,

238
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:56,600
the company will protect you at all costs.

239
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:59,360
If we have to choose between Ice and you,

240
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:00,960
the company will still choose you.

241
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:06,480
Listen up.

242
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:11,000
What you’re choosing is your work plan,

243
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:13,349
not me.

244
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,000
That’s true,

245
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:18,000
but if you want me to
follow your work plan,

246
00:17:18,069 --> 00:17:19,880
you must handle it just as you told me.

247
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,829
Try figuring out the solution, Thame.

248
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:24,000
If you want the company to handle it,

249
00:17:24,589 --> 00:17:26,040
this is the only way possible.

250
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:38,920
Damn it.

251
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:48,840
What’s up, troublemaker?

252
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:49,920
Mick,

253
00:17:50,520 --> 00:17:51,600
where did you take Po?

254
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:54,160
- Did you fire him? - Yeah.

255
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,000
Hey,

256
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:57,920
he works a lot better than you.

257
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,560
What are you talking about?

258
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:01,320
Nobody works better than I do.

259
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:03,056
If there wasn’t someone like me,

260
00:18:03,080 --> 00:18:06,960
would there even be an example
of "easy work with good pay"?

261
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:08,720
But don’t worry.

262
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:12,520
Why would I ask Miss Pemika to fire him?

263
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:14,680
Having him here makes my
life even more comfortable.

264
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,600
Huh?

265
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:19,920
But you said "yeah"?

266
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,680
I mean, I moved him from working with MARS

267
00:18:22,760 --> 00:18:24,320
to working with Ice now.

268
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:48,560
Bro, can you go grab my bag for me, please?

269
00:18:48,640 --> 00:18:50,760
- It’s downstairs. - Oh, sure.

270
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:15,240
You’re all right?

271
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:17,240
Are you okay?

272
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:23,680
Thame, relax.

273
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:25,640
I’m totally fine.

274
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:32,520
Thank you for coming to see me

275
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:36,120
while it’s really such a mess out there.

276
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,480
I just want to make sure

277
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:41,720
