340
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:44,840
Shit. What if someone
really wants to be an idol?

341
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:47,376
Aren’t there any other
choices for them about the rules?

342
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:48,400
The point is,

343
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:52,000
Per and I dating someone doesn’t mean

344
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:54,600
we love our fans less than before.

345
00:24:56,640 --> 00:24:58,240
What we’re doing now,

346
00:24:58,320 --> 00:24:59,680
trying to keep the group going,

347
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:02,800
isn’t just for ourselves.

348
00:25:03,600 --> 00:25:04,960
We’re doing it for our fans, too.

349
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:10,680
I’m totally fine with
everything you guys said,

350
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:13,440
but I’m just wondering

351
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:15,920
if this buzz can really help
our song climb up the chart.

352
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:23,120
I’ll consult with Gam.

353
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:26,520
Fern,

354
00:25:27,080 --> 00:25:29,080
I understand how awful
you must be feeling now,

355
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:30,840
but let me ask you something.

356
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:34,000
Does the fact that he’s dating

357
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,320
make you like him less?

358
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:41,440
Frankly speaking,

359
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:43,560
